T1	Participants 516 629	Caregivers (n = 77) of the cognitively impaired living at home were randomized to receive nurse counseling or not
T2	Participants 1271 1473	Caregivers in control and counseling groups whose relatives entered a nursing home improved their psychosocial adjustment 23% on average whereas those continuing to live in the community decreased by 8%
T3	Participants 1475 1721	Almost half as many relatives entered nursing homes in the counseling group (n = 9 vs. n = 5) but these compared to control group relatives had greater annualized per person expenditures for health and social services (Cdn$23,437 vs. Cdn$15,151).
